{
  "text": "Finally, particular TP dimensions may foster different coping strategies (cf. [CITATION_1] . By their nature, Past-Negative and Future-Negative dimensions should promote emotion-oriented coping (see [CITATION_2] , whereas avoidance-oriented coping seem highly probable in present-oriented individuals, as both present dimensions are positively related to avoidant procrastination [CITATION_3] . Future-Positive should naturally foster task-oriented coping (see [CITATION_4] , for a broad rationale for expecting this association).",
